mocDescription: This is a MOC of the JUICE spacecraft in 1:40. It features a Jupiter themed stand for the spacecraft and the solar panels.

versions.changelog: Add support for solar panels, as they are too heavy.

mocDescription:
This is a MOC of the Titan IVB rocket. The boosters can be separated from the core stage and the second stage, which can also be separated from the core stage. The fairing holds space for a payload. The MOC also includes a black stand.
 There are five variants, each with a different fairing height and with either an IUS, a Centaur or no upper stage.
rocketDescription: The Titan IVB was the last rocket of the Titan series. It was launched a total of 17 times between 1997 and 2005. It could carry an IUS or a Centaur upper stage.
partsExtra: 866,918,934,965,981 parts depending on the fairing size. Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Titan IVB

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Titan IIIC rocket as it looked like on its final flight with the Vela 11 and 12 satellites onboard. The boosters can be separated from the core stage. The second stage can be separated from the core stage and the third stage (transtage) can again be separated from the second stage. The fairing contains the included Vela 11 and 12 satellites.
rocketDescription: This final Titan IIIC was launched in 1970. The Titan IIIC rocket was manufactured by Martin. It was first launched in 1965 and its last launch was in 1970. The first stage is powered by a LR-87-AJ-9 rocket engine with two solid fuel boosters. The second stage is powered by a LR-91-AJ-9 and the third stage is the transtage which is powered by two AJ-10-138s.
partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Titan IIIC Vela 11 and 12

rocketDescription: The Starliner spacecraft is Boeings newest reusable crewed spaccecraft. In 2019 it first launched on an uncrewed test flight. The Atlas V rocket is the newest rocket of the Atlas series of rockets. With a first flight in 2002 it flew almost 100 times since then. The rocket is made up out of a first stage with a RD-180 rocket engine, using RP-1/LOX as fuel and oxidizer. The first stage can also have up to 5 solid rocket boosters. mocDescription: The Orion spacecraft and ICPS can be seperated. This MOC furthermore includes a display stand. If you intend to build this MOC, I recommend buying good quality bricks and some parts benefit greatly by having bricks with high clutch power and accurate casts due to the techniques used.
rocketDescription: The Orion spacecraft was launches on the SLS rocket around the moon in December 2022. The ICPS (Interim Cryogenic Propulsion Stage) functioned as an upper stage to boost Orion into Orbit and to the moon. It uses a snigle RL-10 engine and runs on liquid hydrogen and liquid oxygen. The ICPS is a stretched version of the Delta Cryogenic Second Stage which is being used on the Delta IV rocket.
partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Orion with ICPS
difficultyExtra: I strongly recommend using high quality parts for this MOC!

mocDescription: The Ariane 5 ECA (Evolution Cryotechnique Type A) is the latest version of the Ariane 5 launcher. It can launch up to 10.9 tons in GTO. It first flew in 2002 and will fly it's last flight in 2023. It is known for launching the James Webb Space Telscope as well as many communication satellites.
title: Ariane 5 ECA
